The paper focuses on investigating the impact of technical domain expertise on search behavior and task outcome, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study also involves constructing expertise tests, which could be related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for more effective use of expert behavior in search logs, which could be related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) in terms of detecting and preventing malicious search behavior.
